═══════════════════════════════════
1. Bollinger Bands + Z-Score       |
═══════════════════════════════════
1 - bollinger bands

this bands kinda show you where the price is placed based on SMA & STD
--> the price moving average and volatilty can determine like a range 
FORMULA:
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 
  SMA        = average of last 20 closing prices
  STD        = standard deviation of last 20 closing prices
 
    upper band = SMA + (k * STD) ← abnormally high zone
    lower band = SMA - (k * STD) ← abnormally low zone
    > where k is the number of stds you move away from the SMA to compute the band
 
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-->as a result you get two bands and the price of today lives between them
    > if the price is near upper band it's overbought --> it will go back dowm
    > if the price is near lower band it's oversold --> it will go back up

2 - Z-score 

then comes the z score to tell you how strong that move is :
it uses STD to tell you based on the fluctuation of the price how far the price is from the mean

z = (price of today - SMA )/ STD
                    ↑
          how many standard deviations away from average

we have a treshold of 1.5 z_score 

if z < treshold it is oversold
if z > treshold it is overbought
if it crossed 0 between yesterday and today then prices went back to their mean already you exit immediatly

Bollinger Bands + Z-Score answer ONE question:
    "How far is the price from its average, and is it extreme enough to act?"
They tell you: whether the price has moved into an abnormal zone
               AND exactly how extreme the deviation is.
BUY when:
    price <= Lower_band   AND   Z < -1.5
Meaning:
Price is at bottom extreme (BB)
AND far below mean (Z-score)

SELL when:
    price >= Upper_band   AND   Z > 1.5
Meaning:
Price is at top extreme
AND far above mean

z_strong is a boost of confidence and prove the strength of the move 
--> treshold is 2 if z_score went beyond it up or down boost the confidence 

| |Z| range              | Confidence      | Explanation                   |
  | :------------------- | :-------------- | :---------------------------- |
  | |Z| ≤ 1.5             | 0.55 (floor)    | at threshold, minimum strength|
  | 1.5 < |Z| ≤ 2.2       | 0.55 → 0.80     | linear ramp as Z grows        |
  | |Z| > 2.2             | 0.80 → 0.88     | strong boost, capped at 0.88  |


══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
GOLDEN RULE
 
  Z below −1.5 + price below Lower Band → oversold   → BUY
  Z above +1.5 + price above Upper Band → overbought → SELL
  Z between −1.5 and +1.5              → neutral    → HOLD
 
  Bands show WHERE the price is.
  Z-Score shows HOW EXTREME the deviation is.
  You need BOTH to fire a signal.
 
