3. BandWidth & BandWidth_Change                |
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
 
BandWidth answers ONE question:
    "Are the Bollinger Bands expanding fast right now?"
 
It tells you: is a big breakout move starting?
              If yes, mean reversion is dangerous.
 
  BandWidth stable or contracting → mean reversion likely to work   ✅
  BandWidth expanding rapidly     → breakout starting, don't trade  ❌
 
ANALOGY:
  Contracting bands = calm before the storm → reversals work
  Expanding bands   = storm has already arrived → don't trade against it
 
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 
FORMULA:
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 
  BandWidth        = (Upper Band − Lower Band) / SMA
                          ↑
              normalized width (removes price scale)
 
  BandWidth_Change = pct_change(BandWidth)
                          ↑
              how fast the bands are expanding TODAY vs yesterday
 
  BandWidth_Change ≥ 0.03 (3%) → expanding rapidly → BLOCK entry
 
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 
